            <div class="story-promo__info" dir="auto">
                <strong class="story-promo__hed">Years After Being Ticketed at School for a Theft She Said Never Happened, Former Student Prevails in Court</strong>
                            </div>
        </a>

    
</aside>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="27.0">Naperville spokesperson Linda LaCloche has previously denied that race played a role in Harris’ case or in police decisions to ticket students. The school district has distanced itself from the case and has said the Naperville police decide whether to ticket students.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="28.0">Since police issued her the ticket, Harris graduated early from high school, earned an associate’s degree from a community college, studied abroad in Japan and graduated with a bachelor’s degree in international studies. She said she plans to apply to veterinary school.</p>
        
    
                    
    
    
