        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/guns-chicago-police-ella-french-indiana-tiahrt-amendment">
                                    Even When a Cop Is Killed With an Illegally Purchased Weapon, the Gun Store’s Name Is Kept Secret
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            A 2003 law pushed by the gun industry limits the information shared by federal agents and shields gun shops from public scrutiny, but ProPublica was able to identify the store that sold the gun used in the shooting of a Chicago police officer.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/vernal-coleman">Vernal Coleman</a>, photography by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/sarahbeth-maney">Sarahbeth Maney</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-05-14EDT05:00">May 14, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

